flowRoot.flowPara: After diagonalizing the inertia tensor, we create a new basis set for the inertia tensor that use a recombination of y and z unit vectors to create two new unit vectors, $\hat{b}$ and $\hat{c}$. The $\hat{a}$ unit vector is essentially the same as $\hat{x}$ unit vector
Non-diagonal Inertia tensor using $\hat{x}$, $\hat{y}$, and $\hat{z}$ as basis set
Diagonal Inertia tensor using $\hat{a}$, $\hat{b}$, and $\hat{c}$ basis set
Angular velocity about the y and z result in angular momentum consisting of y and z components.
Rotation about the $\hat{x}$ results in a parallel angular momentum.
